iv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20Kazan%20chaired%20by%20Russia%20has%20drawn%20great%20international%20attention%20because%20it%20conveys%20many%20messages%20in%20the%20current%20geopolitical%20context%20and%20that%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20has%20tried%20to%20isolate%20Russia%20internationally%2C%20defeat%20it%20militarily%2C%20and%2C%20through%20an%20array%20of%20draconian%20sanctions%2C%20cause%20its%20economic%20collapse.%20None%20of%20these%20objectives%20have%20been%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20ties%20with%20China%20have%20deepened%20strategically.%20India%20has%20preserved%20its%20strategic%20ties%20with%20Moscow%20despite%20western%20pressure.%20Russia's%20ties%20with%20several%20African%20countries%20also%20have%20a%20new%20momentum.%20Moscow%20is%20strongly%20present%20in%20the%20West%20Asia%20region%20and%20has%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20key%20Arab%20countries.%20Its%20partnership%20with%20some%20ASEAN%20countries%20is%20gathering%20steam%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Expansion%20Of%20BRICS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20in%202023%2C%20with%20Egypt%2C%20UAE%2C%20Iran%2C%20Ethiopia%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20had%20already%20signalled%20how%20major%20countries%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20viewed%20Russia%20very%20differently%20from%20how%20the%20West%20saw%20it.%20The%20Global%20South%20sees%20Russia%20as%20a%20friendly%20country%2C%20not%20an%20adversary.%20That%20almost%2040%20countries%20have%20shown%20interest%20in%20joining%20BRICS%2C%20a%20forum%20in%20which%20Moscow%20plays%20a%20key%20role%2C%20signifies%20that%20for%20them%2C%20Russia%20is%20an%20attractive%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20countries%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20seek%20a%20reformed%20international%20system%20that%20would%20reflect%20the%20shifts%20in%20power%20equations%20away%20from%20the%20West%2C%20both%20economic%20and%20political%2C%20that%20have%20occurred%20over%20the%20years.%20They%20want%20more%20attention%20to%20be%20paid%20to%20their%20concerns%20and%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hypocrisy%20and%20double%20standards%20of%20the%20West's%20%E2%80%9Cvalues-based%E2%80%9D%20policies%2C%20its%20military%20interventions%20and%20the%20use%20of%20various%20means%20to%20bring%20about%20regime%20changes%2C%20the%20use%20of%20sanctions%20as%20a%20policy%20tool%2C%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20the%20dollar%20and%20the%20global%20financial%20system%20by%20the%20US%2C%20have%20increasingly%20pushed%20non-Western%20countries%20to%20hedge%20themselves%20against%20western%20pressures%20by%20joining%20forums%20such%20as%20BRICS.%20If%20Russia%20earlier%20looked%20westwards%2C%20the%20West%20has%20turned%20its%20back%20on%20Russia%2C%20and%20now%20Russia%20is%20much%20more%20focused%20on%20its%20Eurasian%20identity%20and%20is%20looking%20eastwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENon-western%20countries%20cannot%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20existing%20international%20system%20or%20create%20one%20of%20their%20own.%20What%20they%20hope%20to%20do%20is%20to%20change%20the%20balance%20of%20power%20within%20the%20existing%20system%20and%20reform%20it%20to%20ensure%20more%20equality%20and%20equity%20in%20its%20functioning.%20The%20Global%20South%20countries%2C%20which%20also%20have%20close%20relations%20with%20the%20West%2C%20are%20being%20attracted%20to%20join%20BRICS%20or%20associate%20with%20it%20in%20order%20to%20increase%20their%20political%2C%20economic%20and%20security%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%2024%20world%20leaders%20having%20attended%20the%20Kazan%20summit%2C%20including%20those%20of%20five%20founding%20members%20and%20the%20four%20new%20permanent%20members%2C%20the%20West's%20already%20failing%20efforts%20to%20isolate%20President%20Putin%20and%20Russia%20have%20been%20strongly%20rebuffed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20Members%20May%20Bring%20Complications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20much%20interest%20in%20BRICS%20in%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20the%20question%20of%20expanding%20its%20membership%20and%20the%20criteria%20for%20that%20have%20posed%20difficulties.%20BRICS%20is%20a%20consensus-based%20forum.%20With%20the%20expansion%2C%20building%20a%20consensus%20on%20issues%20would%20become%20more%20difficult%2C%20and%20that%20would%20affect%20the%20working%20and%20credibility%20of%20the%20forum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20BRICS%20Foreign%20Ministers%20in%20June%202024%20at%20Nizhny%20Novgorod%20in%20Russia%2C%20also%20attended%20by%20the%20four%20new%20members%2C%20could%20not%20issue%20a%20joint%20communiqu%C3%A9%20because%20of%20differences%20on%20certain%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Putin%20has%20himself%20publicly%20recognised%20the%20downside%20to%20any%20further%20expansion%20when%20he%20noted%20that%20the%20existing%20members%20have%20now%20worked%20together%20for%20years%20and%20know%20how%20the%20forum%20functions%2C%20and%20that%20the%20process%20of%20absorbing%20the%20new%20members%20into%20the%20methods%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20forum%20will%20be%20the%20immediate%20focus%2C%20not%20its%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%2C%20therefore%2C%20has%20been%20not%20to%20broaden%20the%20BRICS%20membership%20for%20the%20moment%20but%20to%20enlarge%20its%20base%20by%20accepting%20new%20countries%20as%20partners.%20Developing%20a%20consensus%20within%20BRICS%20on%20which%20countries%20should%20be%20admitted%20as%20partners%20was%20presumably%20not%20an%20easy%20exercise%2C%20as%20all%20the%20BRICS%20members%2C%20old%20and%20new%2C%20had%20effective%20veto%20rights.%20It%20had%20to%20be%20ensured%20that%20no%20member%20country%20was%20particularly%20advantaged%20by%20the%20choice%20of%20partners%20and%20that%20the%20final%20list%20reflected%20a%20balance%20between%20the%20preferences%20of%20the%20forum's%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Wide%20Spread%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirteen%20new%20BRICS%20partners%20have%20been%20accepted%20at%20Kazan%E2%80%94Algeria%2C%20Belarus%2C%20Bolivia%2C%20Cuba%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20Thailand%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Uganda%2C%20Uzbekistan%2C%20and%20Vietnam.%20That%20four%20members%20of%20the%20ASEAN%20are%20also%20among%20these%20is%20significant.%20Algeria%2C%20much%20to%20its%20disappointment%2C%20could%20not%20become%20a%20member%20when%20BRICS%20was%20expanded%20last%20year%2C%20but%20has%20now%20obtained%20partner%20status.%20Two%20key%20Central%20Asia%20countries%20have%20become%20partners%20too.%20Other%20Central%20Asian%20countries%20could%20obviously%20not%20be%20included%20as%20that%20would%20have%20weighed%20too%20much%20in%20the%20favour%20of%20Russia's%20interests.%20Already%2C%20the%20inclusion%20of%20Belarus%20is%20a%20clear%20Russian%20preference.%20The%20geographical%20spread%20of%20the%20new%20partner%20countries%20is%20noteworthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20obvious%20preference%20for%20Turkey%20has%20also%20been%20accommodated%20given%20the%20latter's%20geopolitical%20importance%20for%20Russia%2C%20even%20though%20giving%20a%20partner%20status%20to%20a%20NATO%20country%20might%20not%20seem%20to%20fit%20into%20any%20normal%20criteria%20for%20deciding%20BRICS%20partnerships.%20Should%20NATO%20get%20a%20foothold%20in%20BRICS%3F%20From%20the%20Russian%20point%20of%20view%2C%20this%20would%20be%20a%20welcome%20political%20development%20in%20NATO's%20eastern%20flank.%20The%20US%2C%20which%20sees%20BRICS%20as%20an%20organisation%20created%20to%20rival%20the%20West%20in%20the%20global%20system%2C%20would%20be%20obviously%20perturbed%20by%20Turkey's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Pakistan%20Was%20Kept%20Away%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20seem%20that%20China%20has%20not%20exercised%20its%20own%20special%20geopolitical%20preferences%20too%20visibly.%20If%20it%20was%20interested%20in%20Pakistan's%20inclusion%2C%20as%20it%20could%20well%20have%20been%E2%80%94if%20one%20would%20recall%2C%20it%20had%20linked%20India's%20SCO%20membership%20with%20that%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%94it%20would%20have%20run%20into%20India's%20strong%20opposition.%20In%20September%202024%2C%20the%20Russian%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Alexey%20Overchuk%2C%20while%20visiting%20Pakistan%2C%20had%20supported%20its%20inclusion%20in%20BRICS%20while%20also%20stating%20that%20such%20a%20decision%20would%20have%20to%20be%20based%20on%20a%20consensus.%20India%20clearly%20scotched%20any%20move%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20Pakistan%2C%20to%20the%20point%20that%20Pakistan%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20been%20invited%20to%20the%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20reservations%20about%20Turkey%20becoming%20a%20partner%20because%20of%20its%20anti-Indian%20positions%20on%20Kashmir%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%20(UNGA)%20and%20in%20the%20Organisation%20of%20Islamic%20Cooperation%20(OIC)%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20role%20in%20blocking%20India's%20membership%20of%20the%20Nuclear%20Suppliers%20Group.%20Eventually%2C%20India%20did%20not%20stand%20in%20the%20way%20of%20Turkey%20becoming%20a%20BRICS%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20BRICS%20summit%20had%20approved%20the%20membership%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20but%20it%20has%20not%20formally%20conveyed%20its%20acceptance.%20It%20was%20represented%20at%20the%20Kazan%20summit%20by%20its%20Foreign%20Minister.%20The%20Saudi%20Crown%20Prince%20received%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20in%20Riyadh%20while%20the%20summit%20was%20being%20held%20in%20Kazan%2C%20which%20tells%20its%20own%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20Not%20Overestimate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20importance%20of%20BRICS'%20expanded%20partnerships%20across%20Asia%2C%20Africa%20and%20Latin%20America%20should%20not%20be%20underestimated.%20It%20shows%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20current%20international%20system.%20Non-western%20countries%20want%20an%20end%20to%20the%20West's%20hegemony.%20They%20suffer%20from%20the%20West's%20self-centred%20and%20arbitrary%20policies.%20Strengthened%20multilateralism%20reflected%20in%20multipolarity%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20key%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20pace%20at%20which%20BRICS%20can%20bring%20about%20this%20change%20should%20not%20be%20exaggerated.%20The%20goals%20of%20BRICS%20in%20forging%20alternatives%20to%20the%20dollar-dominated%20financial%20system%20are%20not%20easy%20to%20achieve.%20Within%20the%20BRICS%20countries%2C%20there%20are%20rivalries%20and%20divisions.%20Their%20political%20systems%20differ.%20Some%20are%20deeply%20anti-West%2C%20while%20others%20have%20friendly%20ties%20with%20the%20West%20even%20when%20they%20seek%20more%20space%20for%20themselves%20in%20a%20West-dominated%20global%20system.%20The%20economic%20disparities%20within%20the%20group%20are%20large.%20The%20policies%20of%20some%20both%20help%20and%20hurt%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20said%20and%20done%2C%20BRICS%20expansion%2C%20with%20all%20its%20challenges%2C%20is%20a%20vehicle%20for%20a%20much-needed%20re-balancing%20within%20the%20global%20system%2C%20which%20India%20also%20seeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730442120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Ff9ot9bng_india-china-russia_625x300_23_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwests-bid-to-isolate-russia-is-failing-6919687%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20importance%20of%20BRICS%20expanded%20partnerships%20across%20Asia%2C%20Africa%2