in-theatres-go-wild-with-superstars-entry-in-ajay-devgn-starrer%2Farticleshow%2F114836837.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20Fines%20Google%20%2420%20Decillion.%20That's%202%20Followed%20By%2034%20Zeroes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussia%20issued%20a%20fine%20against%20Google%2C%20estimated%20at%20an%20astronomical%20%2420%20decillion%20-%20a%202%20followed%20by%2034%20zeroes.%20The%20unprecedented%20penalty%20targets%20YouTube%2C%20owned%20by%20Google's%20parent%20company%20Alphabet%2C%20over%20the%20platform's%20decision%20to%20block%20Russian%20state-run%20media%20channels%20in%20response%20to%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20This%20sum%20far%20exceeds%20any%20reasonable%20financial%20scale%2C%20surpassing%20the%20entire%20global%20economy%20many%20times%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20penalty%20arose%20after%20a%20Russian%20court%20ruled%20that%20Google%20violated%20national%20broadcasting%20rules%20by%20barring%20channels%20from%20Russian%20state-backed%20media%20outlets%20on%20YouTube.%20The%20fine%20is%20compounded%20by%20an%20additional%20ruling%20that%20demands%20the%20restoration%20of%20these%20channels%2C%20with%20the%20fines%20doubling%20each%20day%20if%20the%20platform%20fails%20to%20comply%20within%20a%20nine-month%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20traces%20back%20to%20March%202022%2C%20when%20YouTube%20announced%20a%20global%20ban%20on%20several%20Russian%20state-operated%20channels%2C%20including%20RT%20and%20Sputnik.%20The%20platform%20justified%20its%20decision%20by%20pointing%20to%20content%20policies%20prohibiting%20material%20that%20denies%2C%20minimises%2C%20or%20trivialises%20violent%20events.%20YouTube%20has%20enforced%20such%20policies%20against%20channels%20supporting%20Russia's%20narratives%20around%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20removing%20over%201%2C000%20channels%20and%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20videos%20globally.%20In%20Europe%2C%20restrictions%20on%20Russian%20state%20media%20accounts%20were%20imposed%20before%20the%20ban%20expanded%20worldwide.%20This%20action%20led%20to%20backlash%20from%20Russia%2C%20which%20views%20the%20move%20as%20censorship%20and%20suppression%20of%20its%20state-sponsored%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202020%2C%20Google%20has%20faced%20ongoing%20penalties%2C%20starting%20with%20a%20daily%20fine%20of%20100%2C000%20rubles%20(approximately%20%241%2C028)%20over%20blocked%20Russian%20channels%20from%20Tsargrad%20and%20RIA%20FAN%2C%20two%20prominent%20Russian%20state-affiliated%20media%20outlets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%2017%20Russian%20broadcasters%20have%20joined%20the%20legal%20fray%2C%20filing%20suits%20against%20Google%20and%20demanding%20the%20reinstatement%20of%20their%20channels%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20onset%20of%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20early%202022%2C%20Google%20significantly%20curtailed%20its%20operations%20within%20Russia%20but%20stopped%20short%20of%20a%20complete%20exit.%20Services%20like%20YouTube%20and%20Google%20Search%20remain%20accessible%20within%20Russian%20borders.%20Unlike%20some%20American%20tech%20companies%20that%20fully%20withdrew%2C%20Google's%20partial%20operations%20in%20Russia%20continue%2C%20although%20its%20Russia%20subsidiary%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20several%20months%20into%20the%20conflict%20after%20the%20Russian%20government%20seized%20its%20bank%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20has%20called%20the%20fine%20a%20largely%20symbolic%20measure%20intended%20to%20compel%20Google%20to%20reconsider%20its%20stance%20on%20Russian%20broadcasters.%20Dmitry%20Peskov%2C%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20told%20Russian%20media%20that%20the%20monumental%20fine%20amount%20is%20intended%20to%20attract%20attention%20to%20the%20seriousness%20with%20which%20Russia%20views%20the%20issue%20of%20YouTube's%20bans%20on%20Russian%20media.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20even%20pronounce%20this%20figure%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Peskov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20has%20leveraged%20a%20range%20of%20penalties%20against%20foreign%20tech%20platforms%20for%20hosting%20content%20deemed%20anti-Russian%20or%20pro-Ukrainian.%20Although%20YouTube%20remains%20accessible%20within%20Russia%2C%20authorities%20have%20threatened%20to%20block%20the%20platform%20outright%20if%20it%20continues%20to%20restrict%20Russian%20media%20channels.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730439180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fmg35f038_google-generic-file_625x300_20_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftwo-followed-by-34-zeroes-why-russia-has-fined-google-20-decillion-6918636%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20unprecedented%20penalty%20targets%20YouTube%2C%20owned%20by%20Google's%20parent%20company%20Alphabet%2C%20over%20the%20platform's%20decision%20to%20block%20Russian%20state-run%20media%20channels%20in%20response%20to%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Movie%20review%3A%20Bhool%20Bhulaiyaa%203%20-%203.5%2F5%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730439000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114690601%2Cimgsize-18306.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fmovie-reviews%2Fbhool-bhulaiyaa-3%2Fmovie-review%2F114837280.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F114837280.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EBB3%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20perfect%20film%20but%20it%20delivers%20what%20you%20expect%20from%20a%20Diwali%20family%20entertainer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Renuka%20Vy