%20no%20other%20country.%20The%20nation%20votes%20in%20November%20but%20the%20new%20President%20is%20inaugurated%20in%20January.%20While%20many%20countries%20swiftly%20usher%20in%20new%20leaders%2C%20the%20US%20takes%20a%20more%20measured%20approach%20with%20an%2011-week%20transition%20period.%20Although%20this%20duration%20may%20seem%20lengthy%2C%20it%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20shorter%20than%20the%20four%20months%20that%20the%20Constitution%20originally%20permitted%20for%20the%20transfer%20of%20power%20from%20an%20incumbent%20president%20to%20their%20successor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistorical%20context%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFederal%20elections%20in%20the%20US%20are%20held%20on%20the%20first%20Tuesday%20in%20November.%20Initially%2C%20states%20had%20different%20election%20days%2C%20but%20in%201845%2C%20a%20law%20established%20a%20uniform%20election%20day%20nationwide.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20US%20was%20predominantly%20agricultural%2C%20and%20early%20November%20proved%20advantageous%20for%20farmers.%20The%20harvest%20would%20be%20complete%2C%20yet%20the%20weather%20remained%20good%20for%20travel.%20Certain%20days%20were%20ruled%20out%20for%20voting.%20Sunday%20was%20universally%20recognised%20as%20a%20day%20of%20worship%20for%20devout%20Christians%2C%20while%20Wednesday%20served%20as%20a%20market%20day%20for%20farmers%20to%20sell%20their%20produce.%20In%20addition%2C%20reaching%20polling%20places%20often%20required%20travel%2C%20even%20up%20to%20a%20day%20for%20those%20living%20in%20rural%20areas%20without%20modern%20transport.%20With%20Sunday%20and%20Wednesday%20unavailable%2C%20Monday%20and%20Thursday%20were%20also%20eliminated%20as%20potential%20election%20days.%20As%20such%2C%20Tuesday%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20suitable%20choice.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20four%20months%20to%20under%20three%20months%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20challenges%20faced%20during%20the%20Great%20Depression%20prompted%20leaders%20to%20expedite%20the%20swearing-in%20process%20for%20newly%20elected%20presidents%2C%20reducing%20the%20lengthy%20four-month%20%E2%80%9Clame%20duck%E2%80%9D%20period%20to%20under%20three%20months.%20A%20%E2%80%9Clame%20duck%E2%80%9D%20refers%20to%20an%20elected%20official%20whose%20successor%20has%20already%20been%20chosen%2C%20leaving%20them%20politically%20weakened.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%2020th%20Amendment%2C%20ratified%20in%201933%2C%20officially%20moved%20the%20inauguration%20date%20to%20January%2020%2C%20while%20presidential%20elections%20continue%20to%20occur%20in%20early%20November.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ELogistical%20considerations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOne%20of%20the%20main%20reasons%20for%20this%20gap%20is%20the%20need%20for%20a%20seamless%20transition%20of%20power.%20After%20the%20election%2C%20the%20president-elect%20and%20their%20team%20require%20time%20to%20prepare%20for%20governance.%20This%20includes%20assembling%20a%20cabinet%2C%20developing%20policies%20and%20addressing%20national%20issues.%20The%20time%20between%20the%20election%20and%20inauguration%20allows%20the%20incoming%20administration%20to%20lay%20the%20groundwork%20for%20their%20agenda.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20extended%20transition%20period%20can%20also%20be%20attributed%20to%20the%20Electoral%20College%20system%2C%20which%20determines%20the%20president%20weeks%20after%20the%20popular%20vote%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20system%20where%20the%20winning%20party%20directly%20assumes%20power.%20While%20this%20delay%20means%20that%20presidents%20cannot%20take%20office%20immediately%2C%20the%20winner%20is%20granted%20access%20to%20transition%20funding%20and%20can%20receive%20essential%20briefings%20from%20the%20outgoing%20administration%20to%20facilitate%20a%20smooth%20handover.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730424240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-11%2Fus-voting_650x400_81478643267.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%