0fairly%20well%20off%20with%20wise%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20one%20phrase%20I%20say%20a%20lot%20is%20that%20if%20you%20aim%20at%20nothing%2C%20you%20will%20hit%20it%20with%20amazing%20accuracy%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20have%20a%20plan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Athletes%20really%20need%20good%20financial%20advisors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20can%20fail%20to%20make%20time%20to%20have%20a%20financial%20plan%20in%20the%20hustle%20of%20daily%20life.%20That%20can%20be%20even%20more%20of%20a%20struggle%20for%20actors%20or%20athletes%20whose%20careers%20can%20be%20intense%20and%20short-lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthletes%20have%20a%20particular%20challenge%20because%2C%20unlike%20most%20people%2C%20their%20top-earning%20years%20tend%20to%20be%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2020%20to%2030.%20He%20notes%20that%20the%20average%20player%20in%20the%20NBA%20or%20NFL%20makes%20%24500%2C000%20a%20year%20during%20a%20three-year%20career.%20Half%20of%20that%20goes%20to%20tax%2C%20and%20their%20manager%20gets%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20rest%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20hard%20to%20go%20broke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20wealthiest%20clients%20are%20in%20business%2C%20not%20sports%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20of%20us%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20life%20experience%20by%20the%20time%20we%20hit%20our%20career%20stride%2C%20so%20we're%20in%20a%20better%20position%20to%20plan.%20He%20gives%20the%20example%20of%20a%2040-year-old%20doctor%20who%20hasn't%20saved%20a%20dime.%20That%20doctor%20still%20has%2020%20years%20of%20their%20career%20to%20turn%20things%20around%20and%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%3Esaving%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20help%20with%20your%20money%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-robo-advisors%5C%22%3Ebest%20robo%20advisors%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20start%20your%20ivesting%20journey.%20Institutions%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Frobinhood-investing-review%5C%22%3ERobinhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsofi-invest-review%5C%22%3ESoFi%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20offer%20bonuses%20to%20new%20customers%20to%20help%20their%20savings%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Big%20money%20can%20cause%20big%20problems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20notes%20that%20many%20people%20fall%20into%20one%20of%20two%20categories%20around%20money%3A%20those%20trying%20to%20get%20it%2C%20and%20those%20who%20have%20it.%20It%20might%20seem%20like%20people%20who've%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20have%20it%20easy%2C%20but%20he%20says%20they%20still%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20keep%20it.%20Fame%20can%20also%20compound%20money%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BFor%5D%20athletes%20or%20entertainers%2C%20their%20falls%20are%20more%20publicized%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20large%20sums%20can%20complicate%20people's%20lives.%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20he%20points%20out%20that%20if%20you%20lend%20a%20friend%20%24500%20and%20they%20don't%20pay%20it%20back%2C%20that%20stings%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20as%20much%20as%20a%20celebrity%20who%20lends%20a%20friend%20%242%20or%20%243%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20well-off%20clients%20who%20want%20to%20help%20friends%20and%20family%20out%20financially%2C%20Taylor%20suggests%20they%20help%20their%20loved%20ones%20earn%20money%20themselves%2C%20rather%20than%20simply%20giving%20it%20to%20them.%20Instead%20of%20gifts%2C%20he%20recommends%20giving%20people%20the%20chance%20to%20invest%20with%20you%20in%20exchange%20for%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20elevator%20to%20success%20is%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%